{"created": "2026-03-30T16:33:44.649393", "current_version": "1.0.0", "project": "ESP32 Distance Sensor", "versions": {"1.0.0": {"created": "2026-03-30T16:33:44.649391", "creator": {"program": "sphinx_needs", "version": "8.0.0"}, "needs": {"US_SETUP_1": {"acceptance_criteria": "", "api_signature": "", "arch": {}, "avatar": null, "closed_at": null, "completion": null, "component": "", "constraints": [], "constraints_error": null, "constraints_passed": true, "constraints_results": {}, "content": "**Role:** Maker / builder\n\n**Story:**\nAs a maker, I want to connect the device to my home WiFi and configure the key\noperating parameters through a web interface, so that I can get it up and running\nwithout touching any code.\n\n**Value:**\nThe device creates its own access point on first boot. The maker connects, opens a\nbrowser, enters WiFi credentials and adjusts parameters like target distance and LED\ncount. From that point the device is configured and joins the home network automatically.", "created_at": null, "docname": "10_userstories/us_setup", "doctype": ".rst", "duration": null, "external_css": "external_link", "external_url": null, "has_dead_links": false, "has_forbidden_dead_links": false, "header_file": "", "id": "US_SETUP_1", "id_prefix": null, "is_external": false, "is_import": false, "is_modified": false, "jinja_content": false, "layout": null, "lineno": 4, "links": ["REQ_SYS_NET_1", "REQ_SYS_WEB_1", "REQ_SYS_CFG_1", "REQ_WEB_1", "REQ_WEB_2", "REQ_WEB_3", "REQ_WEB_4", "REQ_WEB_5", "REQ_WEB_CONF_1", "REQ_WEB_SCHEMA_1", "REQ_WEB_LED_1", "REQ_WEB_NF_1", "REQ_WEB_NF_2", "REQ_CFG_JSON_1", "REQ_CFG_JSON_2", "REQ_CFG_JSON_3", "REQ_CFG_JSON_4", "REQ_CFG_JSON_5", "REQ_CFG_JSON_6"], "links_back": ["US_DISPLAY_1", "US_RELIABLE_1", "REQ_SYS_NET_1", "REQ_SYS_WEB_1", "REQ_SYS_CFG_1"], "max_amount": null, "max_content_lines": null, "modifications": 0, "parameters": "", "params": null, "parent_need": null, "parent_needs": [], "parent_needs_back": [], "parts": {}, "post